reviewText: Unfortunately the level of English used is very poor, both spoken and written, making it incredibly difficult to follow the lectures or even understand the questions in the quizes. For the most part, I was random guessing or using common sense rather than being able to actually understand what I was supposed to have learned.

There was a huge language challenge.  It was hard trying to understand the speakers and in trying to focus on what they were trying to say, I missed some of the content on the slides.  Lots of errors and things not making sense because of the language barrier.  I wish I could've seen a full outline prior to agreeing to take the course as some of the topics did not apply to my profession.  Quizzes were terrible- some didn't go with the content on the module.  Questions/answers didn't make sense because of difference in languages.  It was not specific as to if you could choose one or more answers to questions, so they'd be marked wrong.
